<title>FRANCE: Chirac urges BoF to conduct stable monetary policy.</title>
<headline>Chirac urges BoF to conduct stable monetary policy.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-01-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>French President Jacques Chirac and the government called on the Bank of France on Friday to continue to conduct a stable and steady monetary policy, government spokesman Alain Lamassoure said.</p>
<p>They made the comments after appointing Pierre Guillen and Jean-Rene Bernard as new members of the Bank's monetary policy council (CPM).</p>
<p>&quot;The president of the Republic and the government reaffirmed their confidence in the capacity of the CPM and the independent Bank of France to conduct monetary policy in stability and continuity which are necessary for our economy and to achieve our European objectives,&quot; Lamassoure told reporters.</p>
